title: Part (a)
stimulusHtml:
Select a point value to view scoring criteria, solutions, and/or examples and to score the response.

Students must show their work in order to receive the point.
descriptions:
Response does not correctly calculate the size of the labor force as 100 million and/or does not show appropriate work.

Labor Force=Employed+Unemployed=(92 million+5 million)+3 million=100 million MathType@MTEF@5@5@@80D1@

Response calculates the size of the labor force as 100 million and shows appropriate work.

Labor Force=Employed+Unemployed=(92 million+5 million)+3 million=100 million MathType@MTEF@5@5@@80D1@

descriptions:

title: Part (c)
stimulusHtml: Select a point value to view scoring criteria, solutions, and/or examples and to score the response.
descriptions: Response does not state that actual real output is greater than potential real output and/or does not explain that when the actual rate of unemployment is less than the natural rate of unemployment, the economy is operating above full employment.

Response states that actual real output is greater than potential real output and explains that when the actual rate of unemployment is less than the natural rate of unemployment, the economy is operating above full employment.

title: Part (d)
stimulusHtml:
Select a point value to view scoring criteria, solutions, and/or examples and to score the response.

Students must show their work in order to receive the point.
descriptions:
Response does not correctly calculate the cyclical rate of unemployment as 1% and/or does not show appropriate work:

Cyclical rate of unemployment=Actual rate of unemployment − Natural rate of unemployment  = 5%−4%=1% MathType@MTEF@5@5@@90DE@

Response calculates the cyclical rate of unemployment as 1% and shows appropriate work:

Cyclical rate of unemployment=Actual rate of unemployment − Natural rate of unemployment  = 5%−4%=1% MathType@MTEF@5@5@@90DE@

title: Part (e)
stimulusHtml: Select a point value to view scoring criteria, solutions, and/or examples and to score the response.
descriptions: Response does not state that the actual rate of unemployment will decrease.
Response states that the actual rate of unemployment will decrease.
